WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:03.500
CHAPTER V. OF PROVERBS. KING JAMES' VERSION.

00:03.780 --> 00:08.680
This LibriVox recording is in the public domain, recording by Michael Packard.

00:09.400 --> 00:17.240
My son, attend unto my wisdom, and bow thine ear to my understanding, that thou mayest

00:17.240 --> 00:23.240
regard discretion, and that thy lips may keep knowledge, for the lips of a strange woman

00:23.240 --> 00:30.800
drop as in honeycomb, and her mouth is smoother than oil, but her end is bitter as wormwood,

00:31.160 --> 00:40.080
sharp as a two-edged sword. Her feet go down to death, her steps take hold on hell, lest

00:40.080 --> 00:45.680
thou shouldest ponder the path of life her ways are movable, that thou canst not know

00:45.680 --> 00:53.140
them. Hear me now, therefore, O ye children, and depart not from the words of my mouth,

00:53.140 --> 00:59.540
remove thy way far from her, and come not nigh the door of her house, lest thou give

00:59.540 --> 01:07.100
thine honour unto others, and thy years unto the cruel, lest strangers be filled with thy

01:07.100 --> 01:14.380
wealth and thy labours be in the house of a stranger. And thou mourn at the last, when

01:14.380 --> 01:21.720
thy flesh and thy body are consumed, and say, How have I hated instruction? and my heart

01:22.240 --> 01:28.180
despised reproof, and have not obeyed the voice of my teachers, nor inclined mine ear

01:28.180 --> 01:34.340
to them that instructed me. I was almost in all evil in the midst of the congregation

01:34.340 --> 01:42.080
and assembly. Drink waters out of thine own cistern, and running waters out of thine own

01:42.080 --> 01:49.000
well. Let thy fountains be dispersed abroad, and rivers of water in the streets, let them

01:49.000 --> 01:56.120
be only thine own, and not strangers with thee, let thy fountain be blessed, and rejoice

01:56.120 --> 02:03.540
with the wife of thy youth. Let her be as the loving hind and pleasant row, let her

02:03.540 --> 02:11.240
breasts satisfy thee at all times, and be thou ravished always with her love. And why

02:11.240 --> 02:17.540
wilt thou, my son, be ravished with a strange woman, and embrace the bosom of a stranger?

02:18.000 --> 02:24.720
For the ways of man are before the eyes of the Lord, and he pondereth all his goings.

02:25.080 --> 02:32.280
His own iniquities shall take the wicked himself, and he shall be holden with the cords of his

02:32.280 --> 02:40.520
sins. He shall die without instruction, and in the greatness of his folly he shall go

02:40.520 --> 02:41.540
astray.

